# Diddy Bird – Game Design

## Core Gameplay Loop (Action → Reward → Expansion)

### Action
The player taps to keep the bird in the air and navigates through obstacles.

### Reward
- Score increases for every obstacle passed
- Visual/audio feedback for success
- tuff elements reward the player with humor

### Expansion
- Game speed gradually increases (COMMING SOON)
- Obstacles become harder and more unpredictable (COMMING SOON)
- Visuals become more distorted (analog horror effect)

---

## Difficulty Curve & Progression

### Early Game
- Slow speed
- Wide gaps between obstacles
- Easy to learn controls

### Mid Game (COMING SOON)
- Faster movement
- Narrower gaps
- More distracting visuals

### Late Game (COMING SOON)
- Very fast speed
- Tight gaps and chaotic obstacle placement
- Heavy visual distortion for difficulty

### Progression System (COMING SOON)
- Score-based progression
- Difficulty scales automatically over time
- No levels, endless gameplay loop
